 the Diaspora is divided into three main sections looking into: the Turkish state and society’s pressures over Alevis; how Alevis struggle and obtain representation in various Western countries; and how traditional authority and rituals transform under these conditions. Studying this minority group’s experience helps to understand oppression and resistance in the broader Middle East.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aAlevis. 4aIslamic Studies. 7aHISTORY / Modern / 21st Century.2bisacsh1 aAkdemir, Ayşegül, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aArkilic, Ayca, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBorovali, Murat, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoyraz, Cemil, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDressler, Markus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGültekin, Ahmet Kerim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKurtarir, Erhan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarkussen, Hege, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOzkul, Derya, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aShankland, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSökefeld, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYikmiş, Meral Salman, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZirh, Besim Can, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aÇayli, Eray, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aÖzdemir, Ulaş, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aÖzkan, Nazli, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 a